Faculty profile




Isaac D. SchersonProfessor EmeritusDEGREE:Ph.D. 1983, Weizmann Institute of Science, Rehovot, IsraelRESEARCH AREAS: Computer Architecture and DesignEmbedded SystemsNetworks and Distributed SystemsRESEARCH INTERESTS: Dr. Scherson's research interests fall in the general areas of parallel computer architecture and applications of concurrent computation. His work on interconnection networks for massively parallel systems involves the development of cost-effective high performance networks capable of supporting thousands or millions of processing elements. In addition, Dr. Scherson is applying the results of his seminal networks research to Intelligent Networks on Chip for Embedded Systems.
CONTACT INFORMATION:

